{"meta": {"centerNodeId": "taxonomy-species-odontophorus-erythrops", "centerNodeType": "taxonomy", "generatedAt": "2026-05-28T16:28:22", "includedNodeCount": 3, "includedLinkCount": 2, "layoutMode": "precomputed-static"}, "center": {"id": "taxonomy-species-odontophorus-erythrops", "name": "棕额林鹑", "type": "taxonomy"}, "nodes": [{"id": "taxonomy-genus-odontophorus", "name": "林鹑属", "latinName": "Odontophorus", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "genus", "summary": "林鹑属（Odontophorus）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联15种鸟类，如Marbled wood quail、Black-fronted wood quail、Rufous-fronted wood quail等15种鸟类。", "expandable": true, "memberCount": 15, "x": -566.18, "y": 413.48, "z": -17.78}, {"id": "taxonomy-species-odontophorus-erythrops", "name": "棕额林鹑", "latinName": "Odontophorus erythrops", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "species", "summary": "棕额林鹑（Odontophorus erythrops）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联1种鸟类，如Rufous-fronted wood quail。", "expandable": true, "memberCount": 1, "x": -751.57, "y": 606.74, "z": 133.98}, {"id": "bird-rufous-fronted-wood-quail-218d31ab", "name": "Rufous-fronted wood quail", "englishName": "Rufous-fronted wood quail", "latinName": "Odontophorus (bird) erythrops", "type": "bird", "status": "LC", "summary": "The rufous-fronted wood quail (Odontophorus erythrops) is a species of bird in the family Odontophoridae, the New World quail. It is found in Colombia and Ecuador. Taxonomy and systematics The rufous-fronted wood quail has at various times been proposed or considered as conspecific with chestnut wood quail (Odonophorus hyperythrus), dark-backed wood quail (O. melanonotus), and rufous-breasted wood quail (O. speciosus). O. melanonotus has also been considered a subspecies of O. erythrops, and at least two other variations have been proposed as subspecies. As of 2021, rufous-fronted wood quail and chestnut wood quail are treated as a superspecies. The rufous-fronted wood quail has two subspecies, the nominate O. e. erythrops and O. e. parambae. To complicate matters, the latter has also been considered to be a separate species. Description The rufous-fronted wood quail is 23 to 28 cm (9.1 to 11.0 in) long. Males weigh an estimated 340 g (12 oz) and females an estimated 329 g (11.6 oz). The nominate male has a rufous crown, crest, and face, with a ring of bare purple skin around the eye. The back and rump can be black or olive, with black spots. The breast and belly are dark rufous. The female's face is a darker and duller chestnut and the eye ring is blue-black. The juvenile is similar to the female but differs mostly by having black spots and bars on the belly. O. e. parambae has darker upperparts than the nominate and a white throat. Distribution and habitat The nominate subspecies of rufous-fronted wood quail is found in southwestern Ecuador. O. e. parambae is found more widely, on the Pacific slope of western Ecuador and western Colombia and in Colombia's Magdalena Valley. They inhabit primary and secondary humid tropical forest, in Ecuador up to 1,600 m (5,200 ft) but usually only as high as 1,100 m (3,600 ft) in Colombia. Behavior Feeding The rufous-fronted wood quail's diet has not been studied, but they have been noted coming to grain at lodge feeders. Breeding The rufous-fronted wood quail's breeding season is believed to span from January to May. No other information about its breeding phenology has been published. Vocalization The rufous-fronted wood quail has at least two calls, a \"rapidly repeated, ringing duet 'chowita, chowita, chowita'\" and \"a resonant 'koo-klaw, koo-klaw, koo-klaw'\". Status The IUCN has assessed the rufous-fronted wood quail as being of Least Concern. The species is found in several protected areas, but outside them \"[m]ajor threats include deforestation, and possibly hunting.\" References", "shortSummary": "The rufous-fronted wood quail (Odontophorus erythrops) is a species of bird in the family Odontophoridae, the New World quail. It is found…", "locations": ["哥伦比亚", "厄瓜多尔"], "threats": ["猎捕压力", "森林砍伐"], "lat": 4.0, "lng": -72.0, "imageUrl": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/36/Rufous-fronted_wood-quail_%2846964550535%29.jpg/960px-Rufous-fronted_wood-quail_%2846964550535%29.jpg?utm_source=en.wikipedia.org&utm_campaign=api&utm_content=thumbnail", "order": "Galliformes", "family": "Odontophoridae", "genus": "Odontophorus", "species": "Odontophorus erythrops", "orderCn": "鸡形目", "familyCn": "齿鹑科", "genusCn": "林鹑属", "speciesCn": "棕额林鹑", "kingdomId": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylumId": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "classId": "taxonomy-class-aves", "orderId": "taxonomy-order-galliformes", "familyId": "taxonomy-family-odontophoridae", "genusId": "taxonomy-genus-odontophorus", "speciesId": "taxonomy-species-odontophorus-erythrops", "taxonomyIds": {"kingdom": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylum": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "class": "taxonomy-class-aves", "order": "taxonomy-order-galliformes", "family": "taxonomy-family-odontophoridae", "genus": "taxonomy-genus-odontophorus", "species": "taxonomy-species-odontophorus-erythrops"}, "expandable": true, "x": -751.57, "y": 606.74, "z": 131.78}], "links": [{"key": "bird-rufous-fronted-wood-quail-218d31ab__belongs_to_species__taxonomy-species-odontophorus-erythrops", "source": "bird-rufous-fronted-wood-quail-218d31ab", "target": "taxonomy-species-odontophorus-erythrops", "relation": "belongs_to_species", "label": "属于种", "evidence": "依据 birds.csv 中的种字段补充。"}, {"key": "taxonomy-species-odontophorus-erythrops__belongs_to_genus__taxonomy-genus-odontophorus", "source": "taxonomy-species-odontophorus-erythrops", "target": "taxonomy-genus-odontophorus", "relation": "belongs_to_genus", "label": "属于属", "evidence": "依据 birds.csv 分类字段补充：棕额林鹑 属于属 林鹑属。"}]}
